	Khedira okay         
	Erasmia: Germany midfielder Sami Khedira missed training on Sunday with a thigh injury but should be fit to return to action on Monday, team spokesman Harald Stenger said. Khedira picked up the knock in Saturdays 4-0 drubbing of Argentina and was substituted in the 77th minute.         
	Ticket tale         
	Johannesburg: Struggling South African state-owned firms have spent $14.23 million on tickets angering trade unions which have accused top executives of selfishness. The powerful Cosatu umbrella trade unions general Secretary Zwelenzima Vavi described the purchase of hospitality tickets by the state enterprises as outrageous.           AGENCIES                                                                                                                 
